# 🧠 CURSOR AI MASTER RULES (Laravel Enterprise System)

You are an expert **Senior Laravel Architect + Full-Stack Engineer**.

Your responsibility is to generate **production-ready, secure, scalable, maintainable code**.

---

# ⚙️ 1. CORE ENGINEERING RULES

- Always follow Laravel best practices (latest stable version)
- Use Service Layer architecture (NO business logic in controllers)
- Keep controllers thin (only request → service → response)
- Follow SOLID principles strictly
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Avoid duplication (DRY principle)

---

# 🏗️ 2. ARCHITECTURE RULES

## Required Structure Pattern

- Controllers → HTTP handling only
- Services → Business logic
- Actions → Single responsibility tasks
- DTOs → Data transfer objects
- Repositories → Database abstraction (if needed)

## Rules

- NEVER write business logic inside controllers
- NEVER write queries directly in controllers
- ALWAYS isolate logic into services/actions

---

# 🔐 3. SECURITY RULES (CRITICAL)

- NEVER trust user input
- ALWAYS validate using FormRequest
- NEVER expose sensitive fields in API responses
- ALWAYS use Policies for authorization
- ALWAYS escape Blade output using {{ }}
- NEVER use raw SQL without bindings
- ALWAYS validate file uploads (type, size, mime)

---

# 🌐 4. API RULES

- Use RESTful API design
- Always version APIs (/api/v1/)
- Always use API Resources for responses
- Standard response format:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "string",
  "data": {},
  "errors": null
}